Is it true that t-tests, ANOVAs and linear regressions are all parametric models?

You have fitted linear regression models in previous workshops. What’s new when we run a t-test or an ANOVA as linear model using lm?

Ooops! Okay granted, this isn’t simple. So far you have learnt linear models with continuous outcome variables (we will cover linear models with non-continous outcome variables next year). ANOVAs and t-test have categorical predictor variables which you called groups or conditions. Those are categories (= categorical). In the lecture (and in the workshop week 18) I demoned how to fit linear models with categorical predictors akin to t-tests and ANOVAs.

Why would we use an linear model instead of running a t-test or an ANOVA?
